  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Patients on a stable dose of ACE inhibitor or ARB medication who are scheduled for elective
      surgery will be randomized to take their ACE inhibitor or ARB up to and including the morning
      of surgery, or to hold them a day prior to the surgery. The patients will be followed for 30
      days after surgery to assess any adverse health outcomes.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
